==English==
alternative spelling: [[stanch]]
===Pronunciation===
[[w:AHD|AHD]]: stônch, stänch
===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''estanchier'', stanch, from Vulgar Latin ''stanticāre'', stop, from Latin ''stāre'', stand
  
===Adjective===
# [[loyal]], [[trustworthy]]
===Transitive verb===
#To stop the flow of (blood)
#To check the flow of
===Word usage===
''staunch'' is more commonly used as the spelling for the adjective.  In contrast, ''stanch'' is more commonly used as the spelling of the verb.